{"type":"message","id":"236d533f","parentId":"6ddc9f78","timestamp":"2026-03-05T06:41:31.709Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We are in a cron job context (session spawned for a scheduled task). The task is to summarize inbox and calendar for today (March 5th, 2026) and return the summary as plain text.\n Since the cron job is set to run in the morning, but the current time is 2:40 PM, it might be a delayed run or we are in a different timezone. However, the task is clear: summarize for today.\n\n Steps:\n 1. We don't have direct access to the user's inbox and calendar. We must rely on the OpenClaw setup to have integrations that can fetch this data.\n 2. However, note that the cron job is running and we are expected to return a summary. We must check if there are any existing files or tools that can help.\n\n But wait: the cron job is named \"Morning status\", so it might have already run and stored the data? Or we are expected to run the checks now.\n\n Since we are in a cron job, we are expected to produce the summary. We don't have the data, so we must fetch it.\n\n How?\n - For calendar: we might have a tool that fetches calendar events for today. But we don't have a specific tool for that in the provided list.\n - For inbox: similarly, we don't have a tool for email.\n\n However, note that the user might have set up periodic checks via heartbeat or other cron jobs that store the data in files.\n\n Let's look at the workspace context files:\n   AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md\n\n None of these seem to contain the data we need.\n\n Alternatively, we might have a skill for handling calendar and email. But the available skills (from the context) are:\n   feishu-doc, feishu-drive, feishu-perm, feishu-wiki, clawhub, healthcheck, skill-creator, weather, find-skills, stock-watcher\n\n None of these seem to cover email or calendar.\n\n Therefore, we must conclude that we cannot complete the task because we lack the necessary tools or data.\n\n However, note that the cron job is set to run and we must return a summary. We have two options:\n\n Option 1: Return a message indicating that the necessary integrations are not set up.\n Option 2: Check if there are any stored files from previous runs that might have the data.\n\n Since the cron job is named \"Morning status\", it's possible that it runs in the morning and we are now in the afternoon. We are running it now because of the cron schedule? But the current time is 2:40 PM. The cron might be set to run at a different time.\n\n But the task says: \"Summarize inbox + calendar for today\". We are to summarize for today, regardless of the time of day.\n\n Without the tools, we cannot fetch the data.\n\n Let's see if we can find any files that were generated by previous runs. For example, the cron job might store its output in a file.\n\n We tried reading '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/daily_summary.txt' and got an error.\n\n We might need to look for other files. However, without knowing the exact setup, it's hard.\n\n Given the constraints, we must return a summary that states the issue.\n\n Summary to return:\n\n \"Good morning! Here's your status for today, March 5th, 2026.\n\n However, note that the necessary integrations for fetching your inbox and calendar events are not currently set up in OpenClaw. Please configure email and calendar integrations to enable this summary.\n\n Alternatively, if you have a different method for retrieving this information, please let me know and I can adjust.\"\n\n But wait: the cron job is running in the context of OpenClaw and we are expected to return plain text. We don't have the data, so we must inform.\n\n However, note that the user might have set up the cron job expecting that the data is available. We must be honest.\n\n Let's return:\n\n \"Status for March 5th, 2026 (as of 2:40 PM):\n\n Inbox: Unable to fetch - no email integration configured.\n Calendar: Unable to fetch - no calendar integration configured.\n\n Please set up the required integrations to get a full status.\"\n\n But note: the cron job might be set to run at a specific time (morning) and we are running at 2:40 PM. The user might have expected a morning summary. However, the task does not specify a time.\n\n Since we are in a cron job and we are expected to return the summary, we return the above.\n\n However, we must be cautious: the cron job might be set to run at 2:40 PM? The name is \"Morning status\", but the time is 2:40 PM. It might be a one-off or delayed.\n\n We'll return the summary as plain text.\n\n But note: the cron job is set to deliver the summary automatically. We are to return the plain text.\n\n However, we don't have any events or emails to report because we couldn't fetch.\n\n Final plan:\n\n We'll return:\n\n \"Good morning! Here's your status for today, March 5th, 2026.\n\n Unfortunately, I couldn't fetch your inbox and calendar events because the necessary integrations are not set up.\n\n To resolve this, please configure:\n - Email integration for inbox summary\n - Calendar integration for event summary\n\n Once set up, I'll be able to provide a full status.\"\n\n But the cron job is called \"Morning status\", so we are expected to deliver in the morning. However, we are running at 2:40 PM. We might be running late? Or the cron schedule is set for 2:40 PM? We don't know.\n\n We'll stick to the facts.\n\n Since we are in a cron job and we must return, we output the above.\n\n However, note: the cron job might be set to run at 2:40 PM because of the user's timezone? The user is in Asia/Shanghai, and 2:40 PM is in the afternoon.\n\n So we adjust the greeting:\n\n \"Good afternoon! Here's your status for today, March 5th, 2026.\n\n Unfortunately, I couldn't fetch your inbox and calendar events because the necessary integrations are not set up.\n\n To resolve this, please configure:\n - Email integration for inbox summary\n - Calendar integration for event summary\n\n Once set up, I'll be able to provide a full status.\"\n\n But wait, the cron job is named \"Morning status\", so it might be intended for the morning. We are running it now because of the schedule? We don't know the schedule.\n\n We'll just say \"Here's your status for today\".\n\n Final output:\n\n \"Here's your status for today, March 5th, 2026:\n\n Inbox: No integration configured.\n Calendar: No integration configured.\n\n Please set up the required integrations to get a full status.\"\n\n We'll keep it concise.\n\n Since we are in a cron job and the output will be delivered, we return this.\n\n However, note: the cron job might be set to run every day and the user might be waiting for this. We must inform the user of the issue.\n\n Let's write the summary as plain text and return it.\n\n But note: the cron job is running and we are expected to return the summary. We have done our best.\n\n We'll output the summary as:\n\n ```\n Here's your status for today, March 5th, 2026:\n\n Inbox summary: Not available (integration not set up)\n Calendar events: Not available (integration not set up)\n\n To set up these integrations, please refer to the OpenClaw documentation or contact support.\n ```\n\n However, we don't have a way to set it up ourselves.\n\n We return this summary.\n\n But note: the cron job might be configured to send this summary to the user via a message. We are just returning the text.\n\n We are done.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I couldn't find a stored daily summary file. Let me check if there's a script or tool that generates the inbox and calendar summary. I'll look for any relevant scripts in the workspace."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d52f010cdee64aa980e257","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find . -name \"*summary*\" -o -name \"*inbox*\" -o -name \"*calendar*\" -type f"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-dashscope-aliyuncs-com","model":"deepseek-r1","usage":{"inpu